# PCG Terrain Generation Graph
# This is a blueprint representation - actual implementation would be done in UE5 Editor

# Graph Structure:
# Input: Landscape Bounds
# -> Surface Sampler (Landscape)
# -> Density Filter (Height-based)
# -> Transform Points (Add geological variation)
# -> Attribute Set (Biome classification)
# -> Output: Point data for Environment Artist

# Key Nodes Configuration:
# 1. Surface Sampler
#    - Sample Mode: Landscape
#    - Points per Square Meter: 0.1
#    - Bounds Source: Actor Bounds
#
# 2. Density Filter
#    - Filter Mode: Height Range
#    - Min Height: 50cm (above sea level)
#    - Max Height: 2000cm (max elevation)
#
# 3. Transform Points
#    - Add geological noise
#    - Scale: 0.1 to 0.3 random
#    - Rotation: Natural variation
#
# 4. Attribute Set
#    - BiomeType: Calculated from elevation/humidity
#    - Slope: Terrain steepness
#    - WaterDistance: Distance to nearest river
#    - Elevation: Height above sea level

# This graph generates the base point distribution that will be used by
# the Environment Artist to place vegetation, rocks, and other props